## How to Start the Bot

### Quick Start
Click the "Run" button in Replit, or use the "Start Bot" workflow.

### Manual Start
```bash
npm start
```

## WhatsApp Connection Setup

### First Time Setup (Pairing Code Method)
1. Start the bot (it will display a pairing code in the console)
2. Open WhatsApp on your phone
3. Go to Settings > Linked Devices
4. Tap "Link a Device"
5. Select "Link with Phone Number Instead"
6. Enter the 8-digit pairing code shown in the console
7. The bot will automatically connect

## Available Commands

### General Commands
- `.help` / `.menu` - Show command list
- `.ping` - Check bot status
- `.alive` - Bot status with features
- `.achek` - Achek Digital Solutions info
- `.pidgin <text>` - Nigerian Pidgin vibes
- `.owner` - Contact bot owner
- `.tts <text>` - Text to speech

### Admin Commands
- `.tagall` - Tag all members (owner can use without being admin)
- `.ban @user` - Ban user
- `.kick @user` - Remove user
- `.promote @user` - Make admin
- `.demote @user` - Remove admin
- `.mute <minutes>` - Mute group
- `.antilink` - Toggle antilink protection

### Owner Commands
- `.broadcast <message>` - Send message to all groups
- `.mode <public/private>` - Set bot mode
- `.sudo <add/remove> @user` - Manage sudo users
- `.clearsession` - Reset bot session

### AI Commands
- `.gpt <question>` - Chat with AI
- `.gemini <question>` - Google AI
- `.imagine <prompt>` - Generate AI image

### Downloader Commands
- `.play <song>` - Play music
- `.song <song>` - Download MP3
- `.video <name>` - Download video
- `.tiktok <link>` - TikTok download
- `.instagram <link>` - Instagram download

### Fun Commands
- `.truth` / `.dare` - Truth or dare
- `.joke` - Random joke
- `.quote` - Inspiring quote
- `.pidgin` - Nigerian Pidgin phrases

